COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Petitioner, v. Elizabeth W. LYMAN, and William H. Lyman, Jr., Executors of the Will of William H. Lyman, Deceased, Respondent. No. 6769. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 7, 1932.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for petitioner, consented to hy counsel for respondent, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered petition to review herein dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
